### Trigger a run — watch the server log for [START], [MAP], [WRITE], [DONE] lines.
POST http://localhost:4106/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments","mode":"delta","trigger":"manual"}

### Confirm the pending shipments were filtered out by the MAP hook.
### The logistics provider has one row with status='pending' in its seed
### data (order 10255). That row should NOT appear here.
GET http://localhost:4106/odata/v4/example/Shipments?$filter=status eq 'pending'

### Active rows landed as expected.
GET http://localhost:4106/odata/v4/example/Shipments?$orderby=modifiedAt desc

### Per-batch metrics — one row per batch of the last run.
GET http://localhost:4106/odata/v4/example/BatchMetrics?$orderby=writtenAt desc&$top=10

### Trigger again — with no upstream changes you'll see 0 rows written,
### but the [START] / [WRITE] / [DONE] log lines still fire.
POST http://localhost:4106/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments","mode":"delta","trigger":"manual"}

### Full refresh — exercises `mode: 'full'`, which re-reads everything
### and re-applies the MAP filter.
POST http://localhost:4106/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments","mode":"full","trigger":"manual"}
